  "title": "refactor(PoweredBy): migrate to TypeScript (part 5)",
  "body": "This is the fifth step toward our process migrating to TypeScript, with an actual refactor to TypeScript.\r\n\r\nThe `CSSClasses` and `Props` types will be shared across the widget and the component in the future.\r\n\r\n### Preact alternative for typing for a functional component\r\n\r\nThis is an alternative (with which the tests fail). I think the one I went for in the PR is fine.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nimport { FunctionalComponent } from 'preact';\r\nimport React from 'preact-compat';\r\n\r\ntype CSSClasses = {\r\n  root: string;\r\n  link: string;\r\n  logo: string;\r\n};\r\n\r\ntype Props = {\r\n  url: string;\r\n  theme: string;\r\n  cssClasses: CSSClasses;\r\n};\r\n\r\nconst PoweredBy: FunctionalComponent<Props> = ({ url, theme, cssClasses }) => (\r\n  // ...\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\n[See more →](https://github.com/scurker/preact-and-typescript#example-usage-1)\r\n\r\n### Related\r\n\r\n- Part 1: #3411\r\n- Part 2: #3412\r\n- Part 3: #3413\r\n- Part 4: #3414",
